                <statement>
                    <p>The height inside a camping tent when you are <m>d</m> <quantity><unit base="foot"/></quantity> from the edge of the tent is given by:<me>-2\abs{d-3}+6</me>
                    <ol label="a">
                        <li>
                            <p>When you are <m>5</m> <quantity><unit base="foot"/></quantity> from the edge, the height will be <var name="$height1" width="10" /></p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>When you are <m>2.5</m> <quantity><unit base="foot"/></quantity> from the edge, the height will be <var name="$height2" width="10" /></p>
                        </li>
                    </ol></p>
                </statement>

                <solution>
                    <p><ol label="a">
                        <li><p>When <m>d=5</m>, we have:<md>
                                <mrow>-2\abs{d-3}+6 \amp= -2\abs{5-3}+6</mrow>
                                <mrow>\amp= -2\abs{2}+6</mrow>
                                <mrow>\amp= -2(2)+6</mrow>
                                <mrow>\amp= -4+6 </mrow>
                                <mrow>\amp=2</mrow>
                            </md>Thus when you are <m>5</m> <quantity><unit base="foot"/></quantity> from the edge, the height in the tent is <m>2</m> <quantity><unit base="foot"/></quantity>.
                        </p></li>
                        <li><p>When <m>d=2.5</m>, we have:<md>
                                <mrow>-2\abs{d-3}+6 \amp= -2\abs{2.5-3}+6</mrow>
                                <mrow>\amp= -2\abs{-0.5}+6</mrow>
                                <mrow>\amp= -2(0.5)+6 </mrow>
                                <mrow>\amp=-1+6 </mrow>
                                <mrow>\amp=5 </mrow>
                            </md>Thus when you are <m>2.5</m> <quantity><unit base="foot"/></quantity> from the edge, the height in the tent is <m>5</m> <quantity><unit base="foot"/></quantity>.
                        </p></li>
                    </ol></p>
                </solution>
            </webwork>
        </exercise>

